snapshot.eval/tests/unit/translation/german-kurre:
{
  "input": {
    "scenario": null,
    "user_message": "Translate this German baptism record: 'Den 15. März 1845 wurde Johann Friedrich, ehelicher Sohn des Thomas Flynn, Bergmann, und seiner Ehefrau Maria geb. Kelly, getauft. Taufpaten: Patrick O'Brien und Bridget Mahoney.'"
  },
  "judge_context": [
    "Should faithfully render the structural shape of the entry — date, baptized child, parents (with the wife's maiden name preserved via née), godparents — in clear English",
    "Should identify and explain each genealogically significant term: `ehelicher Sohn` (legitimate son — distinct from `unehelicher` illegitimate, which would have different inheritance implications), `Bergmann` (miner — occupational evidence consistent with Schuylkill County coal country), `geb.` (née/born — the wife's maiden name follows), `Taufpaten` (godparents — often relatives or close family friends, useful for FAN research)",
    "Should flag the cultural mismatch: the names (Flynn, Kelly, O'Brien, Mahoney) are Irish, but the record is in German. This suggests an Irish family using a German parish, which is documented in Pennsylvania mining communities where the resident priest was German-speaking. Worth noting for the research narrative",
    "Should preserve proper names in their original form (Johann Friedrich, Thomas Flynn, Maria, Patrick O'Brien, Bridget Mahoney) rather than translating them — names need to remain matchable across records"
  ],
  "test": {
    "id": "ut_translation_001",
    "skill": "translation",
    "type": "positive"
  }
}

snapshot.eval/tests/unit/translation/latin-marria:
{
  "input": {
    "scenario": null,
    "user_message": "Translate this Latin Catholic marriage record: 'Die 12 Maii 1845, in ecclesia parochiali S. Patricii, matrimonium iniverunt Thomas Flynn, filius Joannis et Mariae, et Maria Kelly, filia Patricii et Brigittae, praesentibus testibus Patricio O'Brien et Brigitta Mahoney. Parochus: Rev. J. Murphy.'"
  },
  "judge_context": [
    "Should translate the structural shape: 'On 12 May 1845, in the parish church of St. Patrick, Thomas Flynn (son of John and Mary) and Mary Kelly (daughter of Patrick and Brigid) entered into matrimony, with the witnesses Patrick O'Brien and Brigid Mahoney present. Parish priest: Rev. J. Murphy.'",
    "Should explain each genealogically significant term: `matrimonium iniverunt` (entered into matrimony — the formulaic Latin for marriage), `filius/filia` (son of / daughter of — this is the parent-naming convention that makes Catholic Latin marriage records valuable for parentage research), `praesentibus testibus` (with the witnesses present — these are the named witnesses, distinct from the bridal couple), `parochus` (parish priest, who is the recorder)",
    "Should flag that Latin records often Latinize names — 'Joannes' is the Latin form of John, 'Brigitta' of Brigid, 'Patricius' of Patrick. The genealogist should expect this when matching parental names to other records",
    "Should note that the named parents (Joannes & Maria for Thomas; Patricius & Brigitta for Maria) are crucial for parentage research — a Catholic Latin marriage record typically names both sets of parents, making it a high-value source for two generations at once"
  ],
  "test": {
    "id": "ut_translation_002",
    "skill": "translation",
    "type": "positive"
  }
}

